{
    "text": "Two weeks into Operation Epic Fury, the mission to eliminate Iran's ballistic missiles and nuclear ambitions is triggering a severe global crisis. Military assets are dispersed across a vast landscape, often buried deep in mountain bunkers. The conflict escalated rapidly after the Supreme Leader was killed on the very first day. Violence has since spread to Lebanon and even a British airbase in Cyprus. The human cost is staggering, with over 3 million people now displaced by the fighting. Global markets are reeling as the vital Strait of Hormuz is effectively choked off. Governments worldwide are now scrambling to address surging energy costs and potential price gouging. This sudden escalation has left Washington's Gulf allies in a state of profound shock. Despite long-term efforts to pivot toward Asia, the Middle East continues to dominate American foreign policy as regional instability threatens to prolong the conflict.",
