        "segment": [
            {
                "text": "Two weeks into Operation Epic Fury, the mission to eliminate Iran's ballistic missiles and nuclear ambitions is triggering a severe global crisis.",
                "start": 0.16,
                "end": 8.48
            },
            {
                "text": "Military assets are dispersed across a vast landscape, often buried deep in mountain bunkers.",
                "start": 8.72,
                "end": 13.92
            },
            {
                "text": "The conflict escalated rapidly after the Supreme Leader was killed on the very first day.",
                "start": 14.08,
                "end": 18.8
            },
            {
                "text": "Violence has since spread to Lebanon and even a British airbase in Cyprus.",
                "start": 19.04,
                "end": 23.44
            },
            {
                "text": "The human cost is staggering, with over 3 million people now displaced by the fighting.",
                "start": 23.68,
                "end": 28.64
            },
            {
                "text": "Global markets are reeling as the vital Strait of Hormuz is effectively choked off.",
                "start": 28.88,
                "end": 33.52
            },
            {
                "text": "Governments worldwide are now scrambling to address surging energy costs and potential price gouging.",
                "start": 33.76,
                "end": 38.88
            },
            {
                "text": "This sudden escalation has left Washington's Gulf allies in a state of profound shock.",
                "start": 39.12,
                "end": 43.6
            },
            {
                "text": "Despite long-term efforts to pivot toward Asia, the Middle East continues to dominate American foreign policy as regional instability threatens to prolong the conflict.",
                "start": 43.84,
                "end": 52.88
            }
        ]
